    "For comparison, a baseline that utilised two clear infection markers (temperature and Early Warning Score) from the latest guidelines 14 obtained worse results with an AUROC of 0.66, accuracy of 0.61, TPR of 0.75, and FPR of 0.43.",
    "Predictions and labels broken down by IV treatment duration (Fig. 2) shows that the majority of incorrect predictions occurred in the middle of IV treatment days when the models predicted to switch but the real label indicated the patient continued with IV.",
